"So who the hell are you?" Violetta turns to the remaining party of only the people she has never met.

Your- Viotto, however you're related to him, also happens to have been caught up in this. I'll admit the two of us don't really know each other at all, but we're both more or less working together right now to try and find out what's going on. We were going to meet up with another involved group to see if they could help, but we've probably split off from them by this point."
"I guess for now we're just... trying to get back in contact with anyone related to this thing."

Violetta rolls her eyes. "Ha. Working together, hm? You better be pretty confident in what you think you can offer that man. Magnolia, the pathetic woman she is, has basically become his lapdog, and I'm still sure he's just going to leave her behind soon."

Horatius rolls their eyes in response. "Offer *him*? I think you're mistaking the kind of relationship we have. Once he stops being of use to me, he won't be worth my time anymore. Though he doesn't know that, of course."
